            "answer_text": "To Mohammad, In the United States, we use \u201cbest friend\u201d as two words, with a space between. I don\u2019t know any country where \u201cbestfriend\u201d would be correct, although I do see some people using it on Quora. See Billy Kerr's excellent explanation of this from a Scottish perspective. For a related topic, see Sarah Madden's answer to Are the expressions \u201cGood morning\u201d or \u201cGood evening\u201d one word or two? \u2014Sarah M., posted 28 May 2019  QUESTION: Is \u201cbest friend\u201d one word or two words? ",
