            },
            "answer_text": "Two words (one person!). It\u2019s an adjective \u2018best\u2019, with a noun \u2018friend\u2019 making a compound phrase in common use. Latterly dictionaries have taken to including these as \u2018single\u2019 entities, in this case a compound noun. It can be helpful in finding phrases and a bit easier than a thesaurus. Other examples include fast track, sharp bend, super tanker etc. Sometimes of course they evolve into single words. ",
